column5: Up in the 400/11 area from what I understand and another fatality, what is that, 3 this year all in the same area?  Thoughts and prayers go out to the families.
Lots of construction in that area. Most people wont slow down.  Condolences to family and friends.
It happened at Dunlop street, not anywere near the 400/11 split.   400NB was closed for a while today.  That offramp gets loaded and the traffic backs up onto the highway, very dangerous spot.
